02:59:16,004 --> 02:59:18,146
We've had several at Meffitt High School recently.

2091
02:59:18,586 --> 02:59:22,871
And you relied on custodians to go around and look for devices.

2092
02:59:24,451 --> 02:59:27,112
I don't know how that happens, but we relied on custodians.

2093
02:59:27,132 --> 02:59:32,393
So this other pair of eyes you're talking about that are around the building, I don't see it.

2094
02:59:32,693 --> 02:59:34,113
And I think that's ineffective.

2095
02:59:34,553 --> 02:59:46,676
And I think even bringing that up, as Amir mentioned, that you're relying on that as a means of security, shows that you're really not in touch with what security should be and having a secured building.

2096
02:59:47,317 --> 02:59:48,577
So I'm standing here.

2097
02:59:49,648 --> 02:59:51,209
Is anyone protecting you right now?

2098
02:59:51,469 --> 02:59:52,370
Is anyone protecting me?

2099
02:59:52,410 --> 02:59:55,432
Is anyone protecting the citizens of this community right now standing here?

2100
02:59:55,992 --> 02:59:57,534
Anyone could walk in and say anything.

2101
02:59:58,014 --> 02:59:59,415
Anyone could walk in and do something.

2102
03:00:00,476 --> 03:00:04,198
You know, we recognize we live in a society which has some violence to it.

2103
03:00:04,458 --> 03:00:09,382
We recognize we live in a society where there's a lot of random acts of terror and activity.

2104
03:00:10,294 --> 03:00:11,715
But you can't cover everything.

2105
03:00:12,115 --> 03:00:13,856
You can't cover everything realistically.

2106
03:00:13,896 --> 03:00:18,619
And putting a couple of people in the place is not going to be a functional value to us.

2107
03:00:18,659 --> 03:00:20,039
We can get the same return.

2108
03:00:20,800 --> 03:00:21,740
Let me finish the point.

2109
03:00:21,820 --> 03:00:27,263
We can get the same return from people who are asked to look.

2110
03:00:27,303 --> 03:00:27,924
I'll let him finish.

2111
03:00:27,964 --> 03:00:31,806
But, you know, he keeps on saying, he throws out these, we can't cover everything.

2112
03:00:32,126 --> 03:00:33,547
Who asked him to cover everything?

2113
03:00:34,107 --> 03:00:34,787
Thank you, Counselor.

2114
03:00:35,047 --> 03:00:37,529
You know, no one's asking you to cover everything, Mr. Superintendent.

2115
03:00:38,009 --> 03:00:39,570
So, you know, come on now.

2116
03:00:40,132 --> 03:00:41,676
No one's asking you to cover everything.

2117
03:00:41,876 --> 03:00:46,748
We disagree on the functional value of that type of person in the situation.

2118
03:00:47,180 --> 03:00:50,443
But if you want to continue the discussion, maybe the school committee can take it up.

2119
03:00:50,903 --> 03:00:53,225
We can have a discussion, but it's going to require some money.

2120
03:00:53,846 --> 03:01:02,393
It's going to require, what do you call it, an understanding of what they do and how they do it, and whether or not it's really going to give us value or whether or not it's cosmetic.

2121
03:01:03,153 --> 03:01:04,855
So I'm just raising that for you.

2122
03:01:04,895 --> 03:01:09,559
I don't think that in the best of all worlds, we wouldn't have everything we wanted.

2123
03:01:09,599 --> 03:01:10,940
You've raised several things that we want.

2124
03:01:11,500 --> 03:01:13,342
I want a lot of things that I couldn't put in this budget.

2125
03:01:13,782 --> 03:01:15,684
There are people that ask me for things that I couldn't give them.

2126
03:01:16,585 --> 03:01:19,727
okay, in this budget, or any budget.

2127
03:01:20,407 --> 03:01:24,889
I've been doing it for a few years, and I recognize that there are times when you just can't do something.

2128
03:01:25,349 --> 03:01:29,331
I don't think that we are neglectful in this situation.

2129
03:01:29,371 --> 03:01:33,053
I do believe that when we cover the school day, we're doing what we need to do.

2130
03:01:34,213 --> 03:01:35,814
But, okay, look, it's a discussion.

2131
03:01:36,354 --> 03:01:42,377
And I appreciate the fact you care, but I also hope you appreciate the fact that we've thought about it.

2132
03:01:42,837 --> 03:01:44,418
I haven't just dismissed it out of hand.

2133
03:01:44,458 --> 03:01:47,220
I've thought about it, but I don't think it gives us functional value.

2134
03:01:49,021 --> 03:01:49,281
Okay?

2135
03:01:49,901 --> 03:01:50,581
Mr. President, if I could.

2136
03:01:51,562 --> 03:01:52,783
Thank you, Mr. Superintendent.

2137
03:01:53,463 --> 03:01:54,023
Counselor.

2138
03:01:54,103 --> 03:01:59,666
The security of our children relies on secure building.

2139
03:02:00,607 --> 03:02:03,488
And that is a functional value, to have a secure building.

2140
03:02:04,254 --> 03:02:09,418
and to have a functional security after hours, too, when a building's open.

2141
03:02:10,839 --> 03:02:13,601
That's what we have to rely on, Mr. President.

2142
03:02:14,222 --> 03:02:15,323
And that's an important issue.

2143
03:02:16,464 --> 03:02:17,765
And it shouldn't take a back seat.

2144
03:02:18,668 --> 03:02:20,009
It really should take a back seat.

2145
03:02:20,029 --> 03:02:24,873
You know, I wish there was all this dialogue when they hired a $90,000 PR person.

2146
03:02:25,613 --> 03:02:30,357
Where was all this discussion putting a $90,000 PR person in the budget?

2147
03:02:30,817 --> 03:02:33,779
Where was all this great debate saying, can we afford it or not?

2148
03:02:34,540 --> 03:02:40,504
You know, so these are the issues that I don't buy when someone stands up and says, well, we have to make the tough decisions.

2149
03:02:41,245 --> 03:02:45,048
You know, it seems to me those decisions are made, but they're made for political purpose.

2150
03:02:45,902 --> 03:02:52,384
And the tough decision is not going with the political, but going with what's right to do and saying, I need security in this building.

2151
03:02:52,664 --> 03:02:55,645
I need to make sure the doors are secured after hours.

2152
03:02:56,025 --> 03:02:57,786
That's the right thing to do, Mr. President.

2153
03:02:58,046 --> 03:03:12,691
And I'm not going to sit here, Mr. President, and state anything other than the fact that I believe there's a severe security shortfall.

2154
03:03:12,731 --> 03:03:13,091
Thank you.

2155
03:03:13,912 --> 03:03:14,492
At the high school.

2156
03:03:15,413 --> 03:03:16,914
And this superintendent's on notice.

2157
03:03:17,835 --> 03:03:18,936
So, he's on notice.

2158
03:03:19,756 --> 03:03:22,438
And let me tell you, and this is not the first year I brought this up.

2159
03:03:22,799 --> 03:03:27,162
So, when they say they'll have discussion, I've heard this year after year after year.

2160
03:03:27,182 --> 03:03:28,043
There'll be discussion.

2161
03:03:29,844 --> 03:03:30,484
Mr. President.

2162
03:03:30,865 --> 03:03:31,906
Thank you, Counsel Max.

2163
03:03:32,606 --> 03:03:35,688
I just want to comment on something that keeps coming up.

2164
03:03:36,809 --> 03:03:44,395
You know, I've sat here and listened to everyone talk about the lack of communication, the lack of information, the lack of stuff that's going out to the public.

2165
03:03:44,725 --> 03:03:48,768
I want to tell you, that public information officer has put an awful lot of stuff on the street.

2166
03:03:49,148 --> 03:03:51,730
There's an awful lot of information in this community about the schools.

2167
03:03:52,151 --> 03:03:56,574
More information than you've ever had before, and people are telling me that.

2168
03:03:56,914 --> 03:03:57,475
And you know what?

2169
03:03:57,915 --> 03:03:59,356
We can disagree on that, too.

2170
03:03:59,757 --> 03:04:05,001
But the reality is, is that you talk about public information, they're getting it from the schools.

2171
03:04:05,821 --> 03:04:07,142
They're getting it from the schools.

2172
03:04:08,303 --> 03:04:08,483
Huh?

2173
03:04:09,885 --> 03:04:11,886
You'll see the budget soon as you approve it.

2174
03:04:11,906 --> 03:04:12,627
It'll go right up.

2175
03:04:14,107 --> 03:04:15,688
just like it has every year.

2176
03:04:16,468 --> 03:04:22,692
And if you want to change that, you just simply vote to have people put their proposed budgets up.

2177
03:04:22,732 --> 03:04:23,172
That's all.

2178
03:04:23,812 --> 03:04:25,153
But you never did that.

2179
03:04:25,213 --> 03:04:27,154
All you did was ask, what do you call it, to put the money up.

2180
03:04:27,174 --> 03:04:29,155
That was a perfect statement, the superintendent just said.

2181
03:04:29,475 --> 03:04:32,037
Just like we have seen year after year.

2182
03:04:32,737 --> 03:04:34,778
That's exactly what this government's all about.

2183
03:04:34,858 --> 03:04:35,579
Thank you, counsel.

2184
03:04:35,959 --> 03:04:37,820
Just as we've done it year after year.

2185
03:04:37,840 --> 03:04:38,020
Thank you.

2186
03:04:38,880 --> 03:04:39,821
Madam Vice President.

2187
03:04:40,261 --> 03:04:41,562
While the superintendent was up there,

2188
03:04:42,275 --> 03:04:43,736
I was going to bring up the same point.

2189
03:04:44,076 --> 03:04:56,163
I think that having security after 3.30 and on weekends to protect 13, 14, 15, 16, 17-year-olds is much more important than a school blog.

2190
03:04:56,183 --> 03:05:08,591
I was going to ask the opinion on that, because I believe maintenance and security is far more important than having a PR person.

2191
03:05:08,991 --> 03:05:10,272
Thank you, Madam Vice President.

2192
03:05:11,567 --> 03:05:12,148
Councilor Knight.

2193
03:05:12,468 --> 03:05:13,769
Move the previous question, Mr. President.

2194
03:05:15,210 --> 03:05:19,354
Question moved by Councilor Knight that all debate end.

2195
03:05:19,714 --> 03:05:21,315
Mr. Clerk, call the roll.

2196
03:05:21,655 --> 03:05:21,936
No.

2197
03:05:22,216 --> 03:05:23,297
There's a motion on the floor.

2198
03:05:23,337 --> 03:05:24,498
Mr. Clerk, call the roll.

2199
03:05:24,718 --> 03:05:28,581
