03:05:28,601 --> 03:05:30,783
10-minute rule is in application.

2201
03:05:31,344 --> 03:05:34,766
Mr. Citizen, please state your name and address for the record.

2202
03:05:34,786 --> 03:05:37,309
My name is Robert Pentez, Zero Summit Road, Medford, Mass.

2203
03:05:37,469 --> 03:05:38,990
I'm a member of the Saugus body.

2204
03:05:39,455 --> 03:05:45,478
You know, during this past campaign for the mayor's office, the term that the president and mayor used was partners in progress.

2205
03:05:45,538 --> 03:05:51,142
And partners in progress doesn't seem to be the staple that took place during this particular budgetary season.

2206
03:05:51,282 --> 03:05:59,366
As Councilor Lungo-Kern has alluded to, if you only got three minutes of the mayor and the initial presentation of a budget, and then you had to fend for yourself after the fact.

2207
03:05:59,866 --> 03:06:06,270
And I think one of the comments, and I don't know what councilor made it, that many, many questions were asked more this year than ever before.

2208
03:06:06,640 --> 03:06:09,141
This probably is a result of the answers worth forthcoming.

2209
03:06:09,221 --> 03:06:10,562
That's why you ask so many questions.

2210
03:06:11,402 --> 03:06:19,606
But a few of the things that I'd like to highlight, and this particular budget starts going back to a year ago, when this former budget was being presented by Louise Miller.

2211
03:06:20,146 --> 03:06:28,790
The question was asked of her twice, and it was by myself, when Mr. Scarpelli, Council Counsel Scott Scarpelli is sitting, would you present the budget in the same way it has been presented?

2212
03:06:28,830 --> 03:06:29,571
And she said no.

2213
03:06:30,031 --> 03:06:32,452
And we went through the idea of presenting the budget that had

2214
03:06:33,262 --> 03:06:38,924
a wish list of a cost analysis of each and every department had bringing forth that for which they wanted.

2215
03:06:39,444 --> 03:06:40,605
Now you didn't get it this year.

2216
03:06:40,645 --> 03:06:41,525
And unfortunately, why?

2217
03:06:41,585 --> 03:06:55,530
I don't know, because you have the same mayor who was the former budget director who relinquished that position to give it to Louise mill, who presented the budget, who indicated to you at that point in time that you would be getting hopefully a budget that would handle the request of the council that you didn't get.

2218
03:06:56,070 --> 03:06:59,491
But I guess we're talking about old school and it just didn't come to fruition.

2219
03:07:00,093 --> 03:07:18,000
So some of the things that I would be concerned about if I was still sitting on your side would be a new police station, something that you, Councilor De La Ruza, alluded to some three to four years ago as the number one priority of the Memphis City Council, a brand new police station for the police officers of this city and for the safety and the concern of the citizens of this community.

2220
03:07:18,740 --> 03:07:20,140
Absolutely no discussion about it.

2221
03:07:21,301 --> 03:07:23,722
It was a bone of contention during this past campaign.

2222
03:07:24,182 --> 03:07:27,243
President's administration says it would be a minimum of seven years out.

2223
03:07:27,667 --> 03:07:30,168
And we all know right now what's going on in that police station.

2224
03:07:30,208 --> 03:07:31,969
You know, it's rat infested.

2225
03:07:32,209 --> 03:07:33,189
It has mold in it.

2226
03:07:33,569 --> 03:07:35,330
It has police officers that are sick.

2227
03:07:35,390 --> 03:07:40,952
And it just cannot accommodate the everyday needs of a modern society, a police department.

2228
03:07:41,952 --> 03:07:51,836
You know, just a little real quick, when you talked about the box lunches for the workers on Election Day, it's interesting where the mayor found the money to have the mayor's office done completely over.

2229
03:07:52,336 --> 03:07:55,097
But we can't find the money to take care, unfortunately, the people.

2230
03:07:55,417 --> 03:08:01,882
who work on a daily basis, once a year or twice a year, depending on the primary and the final elections that take place.

2231
03:08:02,302 --> 03:08:06,685
You know, I think it's a service, minimal as it might be, that they deserve something having.

2232
03:08:07,165 --> 03:08:23,757
I haven't heard anybody talk about the fact that, I know there's approximately $20,000 in the budget that the mayor is required to put in, and she has to pay the entire cost of what you folks have hired an outside attorney to bring the 61 Locust Street issue to bear in hand, but nobody's talked about

2233
03:08:24,227 --> 03:08:45,563
which has been on the council agenda for many years, of looking at a new fire station on Riverside Avenue and possibly looking at a satellite fire station that sits on the opposite side of Wellington Station, where the station landing is, where the new development of 200 more units are going up, which are right opposite the Wellington Station, plus the whole commercial industrial area over there.

2234
03:08:45,943 --> 03:08:50,687
And I think that's something that really needs to be addressed, over and beyond the fact that if you look at your budget,

2235
03:08:51,445 --> 03:08:56,028
In this year's budget, your fire department overtime money was there.

2236
03:08:56,788 --> 03:09:01,872
But once again, on the annual basis, on the police department side, their overtime money wasn't there.

2237
03:09:01,992 --> 03:09:04,193
It has to be transferred each and every year.

2238
03:09:04,573 --> 03:09:14,420
Now that's a serious question to ask, because they range anywhere from $400,000 to $600,000 a year in overtime, where the fire department has their money in overtime built right in.

2239
03:09:14,680 --> 03:09:16,801
Why that happens in the police department, I don't know.

2240
03:09:17,141 --> 03:09:19,903
But if you want a true and accurate accounting of what overtime costs,

2241
03:09:20,169 --> 03:09:25,010
or projected overtime costs, that money should be definitive right in there.

2242
03:09:25,530 --> 03:09:29,831
Also, you built a new $14.1 million Department of Public Works building.

2243
03:09:30,391 --> 03:09:35,412
It's understaffed, and you don't have the right equipment to do all the jobs that are necessary on a daily basis.

2244
03:09:35,852 --> 03:09:42,194
Right now, you're dealing with an interim temporary supervisor, a director of the building over there.

2245
03:09:42,574 --> 03:09:43,874
I just don't know where it's going.

2246
03:09:44,474 --> 03:09:48,775
And a lot of this click it, fix it idea of what are being asked to be fixed,

2247
03:09:49,217 --> 03:09:53,318
are being mocked off as being completed, and they haven't even been addressed, they haven't even been resolved.

2248
03:09:53,758 --> 03:09:57,039
And why these things are being resolved through the Department of Public Works, I don't know.

2249
03:09:57,760 --> 03:10:00,681
If somebody's making a mistake or it's an error, for whatever it might be.

2250
03:10:02,101 --> 03:10:12,284
Also, you talked about, Councilman Marks, you also alluded to the fact that $400,000 from the water and sewer on the school department and the city side is basically borne by the taxpayers of this community.

2251
03:10:12,804 --> 03:10:18,346
You know, it's an interesting analysis because many years ago, when we were talking about the new INI that was coming in,

2252
03:10:18,880 --> 03:10:33,024
and we were doing High Street, and the MWRA was in here putting in new water lines, especially at the intersection of Governor's Avenue and High Street, there was a project cost in that particular area of quite a few dollars.

2253
03:10:33,064 --> 03:10:35,365
I forget the exact amount, so I won't lead it to it.

2254
03:10:35,785 --> 03:10:44,407
But part of the mitigation that took place as a result of that is they had to do High Street, I believe from Medford Square, a little bit past CVS,

2255
03:10:44,865 --> 03:10:53,052
to do that street over as part of the mitigation for the cost of putting these two things in there, relining the street and making the connections right there.

2256
03:10:53,472 --> 03:10:58,316
As a matter of fact, I think it was right out in front of Carlings where the sewer just fell into the ground.

2257
03:10:58,356 --> 03:11:01,879
And I think a lady got hurt, and that was precipitous of what took place.

2258
03:11:02,539 --> 03:11:07,343
But the $400,000 is just a drop in the bucket to the $8.5 million that's presently sitting

2259
03:11:07,767 --> 03:11:14,751
and the water and sewer account, you know, and what major projects do you have lined up where those monies can be expended?

2260
03:11:15,011 --> 03:11:16,611
I mean, I didn't hear it, I didn't see it.

2261
03:11:16,631 --> 03:11:32,679
I think last week there was a conversation with some folks on looking at cities and, I mean, streets to be done, and I believe Evans Street was one of them that they were talking about, and I believe the comment was that we'll be getting to the water and sewer portion of it, but we probably won't get to the paving of it until next week.

2262
03:11:33,620 --> 03:11:35,761
I just hope that this council is not getting buffaloed

2263
03:11:36,114 --> 03:11:40,917
and to passing a budget that's not taking an understanding into what streets are going to be done.

2264
03:11:41,258 --> 03:11:45,160
And then all of a sudden next year, in election year, all these streets decided to get done.

2265
03:11:45,480 --> 03:11:47,322
And a major cost is going to come out.

2266
03:11:47,582 --> 03:11:50,644
And maybe this is what this whole capital improvement program is going to be all about.

2267
03:11:50,984 --> 03:11:51,364
I don't know.

2268
03:11:51,825 --> 03:12:03,993
But it's not fair for the people who have been waiting year in and year out, waiting for their street to be done, waiting for their manholes on their street to be fixed, waiting for their sidewalks to be taken care of, waiting for their tree stumps to be removed.

2269
03:12:04,410 --> 03:12:06,872
And the number that you were given a few weeks ago is absolutely wrong.

2270
03:12:07,212 --> 03:12:12,395
There's many more than two to three to 400 tree stumps that are out there that need to be corrected and taken care of.

2271
03:12:13,036 --> 03:12:20,280
You also, um, and in the last election, we talked about the CPA, whether you were for it or against it.

2272
03:12:20,300 --> 03:12:25,384
And here you are in June, almost seven months later, and there's still no definitive program.

2273
03:12:25,664 --> 03:12:30,247
There is still nothing out there to tell the people what that money is going to be used for and when it's going to be used.

2274
03:12:30,654 --> 03:12:39,200
And if you look at the Commonwealth of Massachusetts, they don't even know if they're going to be able to fund it this year, because they're behind on revenues and revenue projections that they had anticipated coming in.

2275
03:12:39,900 --> 03:12:41,981
So the people of this community have to have an understanding.

2276
03:12:42,261 --> 03:12:55,410
If you voted for the CPA for the 1.5%, I believe that's what they voted for, as the override on your taxes, over and beyond your taxes, which to me is an end run of Proposition 2.5, but that's nearly over there, you're still going to be funding the whole thing on your own.

2277
03:12:55,450 --> 03:13:00,133
And you're not going to be getting that for which you thought the match was going to be from the state, because they just don't have the money.

2278
03:13:00,570 --> 03:13:02,570
And unfortunately, you're stuck with it for five years.

